docs.lead_paragraph: Stuart Woods, a prolific, prizewinning mystery writer who churned out multiple best sellers during what his memoir duly described as “an extravagant life,” died on July 22 at his home in Washington, Conn. He was 84.

headline.main: Stuart Woods, Prolific Best-Selling Thriller Author, Dies at 84
headline.print_headline: Stuart Woods, Best-Selling Author Of Many Mysteries, Is Dead at 84

docs.abstract: STUART WOODS of Washington has just had his 19th novel published, his 11th to soar onto the New York Times bestseller list. ''Worst Fears Realized'' is his fifth book to feature the likable though libidinous Stone Barrington, a Manhattan police officer-turned-lawyer-turned-investigator who has a James Bond-ish propensity for perilous predicaments and romancing beautiful women.    This novel, similarly risque as his others, the author acknowledges, is probably extra amusing for anyone who has ever been to Washington, since the pretty Litchfield County hamlet serves as the setting for much of the story.

docs.abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Penn., April 18. -- Stuart Wood, Jr., a member of the firm of R.D. Wood  Co., Treasurer of the American Academy of Political and Social Science, and a bank Director, died a suicide on March 2, not of heart disease, as then reported. The motive remains a mystery to his family and the police.
